[normal]A1 c Suggestion for everyone[bold]•
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Common courtesy.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]A2. A note of concern[bold]Cycling is cheap. And long may it remain so. This means however that the government has little incentive to promote it 
[normal]as it makes little or no money out of it. My concern is that, at the end of the day, the government will be about as keen as to promote cycling as they have been to take effective steps to discourage irresponsible drinking. The amount of tax that goes to t
[normal]he Treasury will probably weigh more heavily with the Government than the nation's health or well-being. This is not a party political matter; the previous government was no better. I am sure that there are a lot of people in government who would be only t
[normal]oo glad if Britain follows the predictions of the "National Transport Model" and the "Cycling Revolution" just never happens.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]December 2013
